# -*- mode:org;coding:utf-8 -*-
#+TITLE: interactors — revise the state diagram between all the interactors
#+AUTHOR: Pascal J. Bourguignon
#+DATE: 2026-07-22

Forked from =interactor-design-revision.issue= (pjb's point-6 answer):
the transitions between the interactors need a full state diagram to be
designed by pjb, rather than more ad-hoc rules.

* Known questions for the diagram

- The §7 install-on-return flow: with =q= above a stop meaning
  confirmed-abort-or-nothing (T4), returning from SEDIT to NAVI with
  the edited definition installed has no dedicated transition. The
  sedit-on-quit save guard (1.4.48) covers the SAVE half (the confirmed
  quit can install), but there is no "install and go back to NAV
  without resolving the stop" edge. An =install=/=done= command? A
  plain =nav= pop?
- Leaving ALDO is a directive, not a pop (T4) — the one asymmetry;
  where does it sit in the diagram?
- navi <-> lavi swapping (D4) is specified as pop+push in the same
  loop but not yet implemented as commands.
- Which modes may stack over which (SEDIT over INSPECT? INSPECT over
  SEDIT?), and what =q= means at each level.

* Current state (1.4.48)

One INTERACTOR-LOOP; activations on =*interactor-stack*=; nested loops
only for invoke-debugger (ui-await-command) and mid-evaluation entries
(sedit-enter, %interactor-mode-loop); directives cascade via ON-RESULT
+ INTERACTOR-RETURN.
